12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9876.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who all is gonna give up EQ for EQ2?</span><hr size=1> I'm surprised no one has mentioned Horizons(www.istaria.com).  For those who enjoy a fantasy theme, it really seems like it will be what many players have been looking for.  Want a change of pace, try playing a dragon, or a half-giant(may not be initially available).  You can choose to be a craftsperson, with a way to advance just in crafting, no need to go out and adventure if what you enjoy is crafting new items, or researching spells for others to use.  <br>
<br>
The difference between Horizons and the other MMORPGs out there and currently in the works is that it's not &quot;Let's make a game that tries to fix what EverQuest did poorly&quot;.  That's the key.  DAoC seemed to be a &quot;Hey EQ players, here's a better fantasy MMORPG than EQ&quot;  <br>
<br>
What others have said about customer support also makes a lot of sense.  We all dislike how poor the customer support is in EQ.  Now, with the player base EQ has, if the support is this poor, what can you expect from a game that doesn't have the player base?  Will it be good because so few are willing to play it, or bad because it's not the &quot;cash cow&quot; that EQ is?  <br>
<br>
Many of us are also critical of the whole class balance and breaking things with expansions/patches issue from EQ.  How many warriors are happy about how difficult it is to hold agro, or how long it took to fix the damage output level of wizards, which went from awesome at max level in pre-expansion EQ, to ok but kinda weak in Kunark, to pretty damn poor in Velious, back to ok from Luclin, and then FINALLY fixing the class with PoP?  <br>
<br>
So, would YOU really trust that EQ 2, even if it was amazing initially, will stay good?  Or will they add a /makeme65 command because someone who plays 1 hour per week can't find groups compared to people who put in more hours to level up?<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
