<br>
Current situation is that Beta 3 for Horizons has begun, and e-mails started going out to people a little over a week ago according to www.tazoon.com(the host of the beta forums).  Since I'm not in beta myself at this point, I have pretty much no information on what's going on with the beta except what's posted.<br>
<br>
I just caught this(was linked off tazoon.com at www.betatests.net<br>
<br>
6-03-03<br>
Horizons to add 500+ beta testers<br>
Artifact has confirmed that we will be adding 500+ beta testers to the Horizons closed beta!!!<br>
<br>
5-15-03<br>
Atari announces MMORPG beta test<br>
Start your coffee brewing because Atari is poised to bring you a beta test for a highly detailed MMORPG Horizons with combat based adventuring and an equal emphasis on trade based community building. With 8+ races and flexible class development your Half-Giant wizard could have a side job as tattoo artist run out of your own house on your own land. Please help us refine this new exciting land.<br>
<br>
You most likely fall info one of three categories. Below are instructions on how to apply to Beta Test Horizons for each of those categories. Much on this information can be found on our FAQ site. Please visit it to get familiar with our system, and it might help to answer many of your questions.<br>
<br>
First time Betatests.net Beta Tester<br>
<br>
If you have not signed up for a beta test here on Betatests.net or on the original Horizons Beta test page www.istaria.com , you will need to do the following:<br>
<br>
1) Set up a Beta test account. You can do this by clicking on the register link in the upper left hand corner of this page.<br>
<br>
2) Fill out an account request. Once done you will have an account on betatests.net and it will never expire.<br>
<br>
3) Apply for a beta test. Once you have registered on Betatests.net, you are always a member (and we do not send out spam). As a member you can now login and apply to any Beta test we are running. If you are accepted you will be notified via mail and given access to the games Beta content pages.<br>
<br>
Horizons Beta tester that Registered at www.Istaria.com<br>
<br>
If you’ve pre-registered on www.Istaria.com, we have migrated account information over to the betatests.net system – your default username and password is your first initial, last name. Once logged in you will need to do the following:<br>
<br>
1) Apply for a beta test. Once you have an account on Betatests.net, you are always a member (and we do not send out spam). As a member you can now login and apply to any Beta Test we are running. If you are accepted you will be notified via mail and given access to the games Beta content pages. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
So, that's the info on it.  Remember, just because you sign up doesn't mean you will get into Beta 3, but who knows.  Good luck.<br>
